headline: How Investors May Respond To Thermo Fisher Scientific (TMO) Expanding Alzheimer’s Registry And Bioprocessing Tools
summary: Earlier this week, Thermo Fisher Scientific reported the first patient enrollment in its new international PPD CorEvitas Alzheimer’s Disease Registry and introduced next-generation Gibco Bacto CD Supreme media and feed to support higher-yield, chemically defined E. coli–based production of plasmid DNA and recombinant proteins. Together, these moves deepen Thermo Fisher’s role in real-world Alzheimer’s evidence generation while reinforcing its tools franchise in gene therapy and mRNA...

headline: 3 Mega-Cap Stocks with Warning Signs
summary: Megacap stocks dominate their sectors and their actions influence economies worldwide. The flip side though is that their sheer size means they have less room for explosive growth as scale works against them.
